text.text: How do streamers set up multiple camera angles?
text.tspan: How do streamers set up multiple camera angles?

text.text: Streamers can set up multiple camera angles using OBS. They stream their default angle to Twitch and send additional angles to the media server.
text.tspan: Streamers can set up multiple camera angles using OBS. They stream
their default angle to Twitch and send additional angles to the media
server.

text.text: What happens when streamers go live?
text.tspan: What happens when streamers go live?

text.text: When streamers go live, their audience will see the main feed while the streamers control the additional camera feeds.
text.tspan: When streamers go live, their audience will see the main feed while the

text.text: How can viewers join a stream?
text.tspan: How can viewers join a stream?

text.text: Viewers can join a stream by tuning in to their favorite streamer’s broadcast to see the main camera feed.

text.tspan: What feature allows viewers to switch camera angles?
